ll]]|timezone=[[Eastern Time Zone|Eastern Time]]|region=C|regionname=Chicago Region}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[2018\u201319 Wright State Raiders men's basketball team]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Wright State Raiders women's basketball navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2018-19 Wright State Raiders women's basketball team}}\n[[Category:Wright State Raiders women's basketball]]\n[[Category:2018\u201319 Horizon League women's basketball season|Wright State]]\n[[Category:2018 in sports in Ohio|Wright State Raiders women's b]]\n[[Category:2019 in sports in Ohio|Wright State Raiders women's b]]\n[[Category:2019 NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Tournament participants|Wright State]]\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n|mode=Women's Basketball\n|year=2018\u201319\n|prev_year=2017\u201318\n|next_year=2019\u201320\n|team=Wright State Raiders\n|image=Wright State Raides logo.png\n|image_size=200\n|conference=Horizon League\n|division=\n|short_conf=Horizon\n|CoachRank=\n|APRank=\n|record=27\u20137\n|conf_record=16\u20132\n|head_coach=[[Katrina Merriweather]]\n|hc_year = 3rd\n|asst_coach1=Tennille Adams\n|asst_coach2=Ashley Barlow\n|asst_coach3=Abby Jump\n|asst_coach4=\n|stadium=[[Nutter Center]]\n|champion=Horizon Regular Season and Tournament Champions\n|bowl=NCAA Women's Tournament\n|bowl_result= First Round\n}}\n{{2018\u201319 Horizon League women's basketball standings}}\nThe '''2018\u201319 Wright State Raiders women's basketball team''' represents [[Wright State University]] during the [[2018\u201319 NCAA Division I women's basketball season]]. The Raiders, led by third year head coach [[Katrina Merriweather]], play their home games at the [[Nutter Center]] in [[Fairborn, Ohio]], as members of the [[Horizon League]]. They finished the season 27\u20137, 16\u20132 in Horizon League play win the Horizon regular season title. They won the [[2019 Horizon League Women's Basketball Tournament|Horizon Women's Tournament]] and earn an received automatic bid of the [[2019 NCAA Women's Division I Basketball Tournament|NCAA Women's Tournament]] for the first time since 2014, where they lost to Texas A&M in the first round.\n\n==Roster==\n{{CBB roster/Header|year=2018|sex=women|team=Wright State Raiders|teamcolors=y|high_school=y}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Nia|last=Sumpter|link=|num=0|pos=F|ft=5|in=11|class=SO|rs=|home=[[Myrtle Beach, South Carolina|Myrtle Beach, SC]]|high_school=[[Myrtle Beach High School|Myrtle Beach]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Alexis|last=Stover|link=|num=1|pos=F|ft=5|in=11|lbs=|class=SO|rs=|home=[[Solon, Ohio|Solon, OH]]|high_school=[[Solon High School|Solon]]<br>[[Ohio Bobcats women's basketball|Ohio]]|cur_rs=yes}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Emily|last=Vogelpohl|link=|num=3|pos=G|ft=5|in=8|class=SR|rs=|home=[[Cincinnati|Cincinnati, OH]]|high_school=[[Mercy McAuley High School|McAuley]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Anisja|last=Harris|link=|num=5|pos=G|ft=5|in=9|class=FR|rs=|home=[[Gahanna, Ohio|Gahanna, OH]]|high_school=[[Lincoln High School (Gahanna, Ohio)|Lincoln]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Shamarre|last=Hale|link=|num=10|pos=F|ft=6|in=2|class=FR|rs=|home=[[Crete, Illinois|Crete, IL]]|high_school=[[Crete-Monee High School|Crete-Monee]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Jalise|last=Beck|link=|num=11|pos=G|ft=5|in=8|class=JR|rs=|home=[[Indianapolis|Indianapolis, IN]]|high_school=[[Arsenal Technical High School|Arsenal Tech]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Mackenzie|last=Taylor|link=|num=12|pos=G|ft=5|in=6|class=SR|rs=|home=[[Richmond, Indiana|Richmond, IN]]|high_school=[[Richmond High School (Richmond, Indiana)|Richmond]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Angel|last=Baker|link=|num=15|pos=G|ft=5|in=8|class=FR|rs=|home=[[Indianapolis|Indianapolis, IN]]|high_school=[[Pike High School|Pike]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|sex=w|first=Dasia|last=Evans|link=|num=21|pos=F|ft=6|in=2|class=SO|rs=y|home=[[Richton Park, Illinois|Indianapolis, IN]]|high_scho